tself-to-google%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Monopoly%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20newsletter%20to%20accompany%20Google's%20adtech%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaparo%20confirmed%20the%20document's%20authenticity%20with%20two%20people%20with%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20the%20matter.%20(Paparo%20was%20a%20DoubleClick%20employee%20when%20the%20document%20was%20produced%20but%20didn't%20have%20access%20to%20it%20at%20the%20time.)%20Business%20Insider%20has%20separately%20confirmed%20the%20document's%20authenticity%20with%20a%20person%20with%20direct%20knowledge.%20This%20person%20was%20granted%20anonymity%20amid%20the%20high-profile%20and%20active%20litigation.%20Business%20Insider%20could%20not%20confirm%20with%20certainty%20whether%20this%20was%20a%20final%20draft.%20Five%20slides%20from%20a%20later%20version%20of%20the%20deck%20are%20also%20included%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstorage.courtlistener.com%2Frecap%2Fgov.uscourts.vaed.533508%2Fgov.uscourts.vaed.533508.1194.18.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrial's%20exhibits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20submitted%20by%20the%20plaintiffs%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoubleClick%20was%20pitching%20itself%20to%20potential%20suitors%20Yahoo%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20AOL%2C%20and%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20hence%20references%20to%20%26quot%3BYMAG%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20deck%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20which%20submitted%20bids%20for%20the%20company%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20with%20direct%20knowledge.%20Google%20won%20out%2C%20paying%20%243.1%20billion%20in%20a%202007%20deal%20that%20officially%20closed%20in%20March%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20and%2017%20states%20claim%20in%20their%20complaint%20that%20Google%20reached%20dominance%20in%20the%20%24300%20billion%20adtech%20and%20throttled%20competition%20by%20making%20key%20acquisitions%20and%20manipulating%20ad%20prices.%20The%20DOJ%20and%20the%20states%20are%20seeking%20a%20breakup%20of%20Google's%20adtech%20business%2C%20which%20could%20have%20big%20ramifications%20on%20the%20broader%20digital%20ad%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20concerns%20the%20under-the-hood%20part%20of%20Google's%20advertising%20business%3A%20The%20technology%20that%20connects%20advertisers%20with%20publishers%20and%20that%20runs%20the%20advertising%20auctions%20that%20take%20place%20in%20the%20milliseconds%20it%20takes%20a%20webpage%20to%20load.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20didn't%20provide%20a%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20%26quot%3BWe%20look%20forward%20to%20setting%20the%20record%20straight%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fgoogle-loses-bid-end-us-antitrust-case-over-digital-advertising-2024-06-14%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20company%20told%20Reuters%20in%20June%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20a%20judge%20ruled%20the%20case%20would%20go%20to%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcerpts%20from%20the%2049-slide%20pitch%20deck%20below%20outline%20how%20DoubleClick%20was%20positioning%20itself%20as%20a%20key%20asset%20to%20help%20a%20potential%20Big%20Tech%20acquirer%20become%20an%20advertising%20giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI%20has%20analyzed%20how%20the%202007%20document%20could%20become%20a%20central%20part%20of%20next%20week's%20blockbuster%20trial%2C%20which%20is%20set%20to%20begin%20on%20September%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDoubleClick%20was%20pitching%20its%20business%20to%20the%20biggest%20players%20in%20adtech%20at%20the%20time%3A%20Yahoo%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20AOL%2C%20and%20Google.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22DoubleClick%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d72fb71d8d2deb96b82e8f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ari%20Paparo%2FMarketecture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDoubleClick%20was%20the%20largest%20publisher%20ad%20server%20%E2%80%94%20technology%20that%20