to%20the%20death%20of%20the%20man%20after%20the%20doctor%20mistakenly%20removed%20the%20man's%20liver%20during%20surgery%20before%20the%20surgeon%20attempted%20to%20pass%20off%20the%20organ%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Benlarged%20spleen%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20lawyer%20representing%20the%20man's%20widow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Facebook%20post%2C%20the%20law%20firm%20claimed%20that%20General%20Surgeon%20Dr%20Thomas%20Shaknovsky%20and%20the%20hospital's%20Chief%20Medical%20Officer%20Dr%20Christopher%20Bacani%20persuaded%20the%20reluctant%20family%20for%20the%2070-year-old%20to%20undergo%20surgery%20at%20the%20hospital%20or%20he%20%26quot%3Bcould%20experience%20serious%20complications%20if%20he%20left%20the%20hospital%26quot%3B.%20Mr%20Bryan%20agreed%20with%20the%20doctors%20and%20underwent%20a%20hand-assisted%20laparoscopic%20splenectomy%20procedure%20in%20August.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20the%20records%20it%20appears%2C%20both%20physicians%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20discussion%20as%20to%20the%20appropriateness%20of%20the%20planned%20procedure%20and%20the%20capabilities%20of%20the%20facility%20to%20accommodate%20such%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20law%20firm%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fplugins%2Fvideo.php%3Fheight%3D476%26href%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.facebook.com%252Fzarzaurlaw%252Fvideos%252F382732311330894%252F%26show_text%3Dfalse%26width%3D267%26t%3D0%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22267%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22476%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20surgery%2C%20Mr%20Shaknovsky%20removed%20Mr%20Bryan's%20liver%20by%20transecting%20the%20major%20vasculature%20supplying%20the%20liver.%20The%20surgical%20cut%20resulted%20in%20%26quot%3Bimmediate%20and%20catastrophic%20blood%20loss%20resulting%20in%20death%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Facebook%20post%20read.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20firm%20claimed%20that%20after%20the%20doctors%20mistakenly%20removed%20Mr%20Bryan's%20liver%2C%20the%20general%20surgeon%20labelled%20the%20organ%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bspleen%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20only%20identified%20as%20a%20liver%20after%20the%20man's%20death.%20The%20surgeons%20meanwhile%20explained%20to%20Mr%20Bryan's%20wife%20that%20her%20husband's%20%26quot%3Bspleen%26quot%3B%20was%20so%20diseased%20that%20it%20was%20four%20times%20bigger%20than%20usual%20and%20had%20migrated%20to%20the%20other%20side%20of%20his%20body.%20%26quot%3BThe%20family%20was%20informed%20that%20Mr.%20Bryan's%20spleen%2C%20the%20root%20of%20his%20original%20symptom%20profile%20upon%20presentation%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20was%20still%20in%20his%20body%20and%20appeared%20with%20a%20small%20cyst%20on%20its%20surface%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20law%20firm%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20inside%20the%20human%20body%2C%20the%20liver%20is%20located%20on%20the%20upper%20right%20side%20of%20the%20abdominal%20cavity%2C%20just%20below%20the%20diaphragm%2C%20and%20above%20the%20stomach%2C%20right%20kidney%2C%20and%20intestines.%20The%20spleen%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20located%20on%20the%20upper%20left%20side%20of%20the%20abdomen%20next%20to%20the%20stomach%20and%20is%20significantly%20smaller%20and%20lighter%20than%20the%20liver.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fneuralinks-first-patient-names-his-brain-chip-eve-uses-it-to-learn-math-and-new-languages-6487096%5C%22%3ENeuralink's%20First%20Patient%20Names%20His%20Brain%20Chip%20%26quot%3BEve%26quot%3B%2C%20Uses%20It%20To%20Learn%20Math%20And%20Languages%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Facebook%20post%2C%20Zarzaur%20Law%20claimed%20that%20Dr%20Shaknovsky%20had%20a%20previous%20%26quot%3Bwrong-site%20surgery%26quot%3B%20back%20in%202023%20where%20he%20supposedly%20removed%20a%20portion%20of%20a%20patient's%20pancreas%20instead%20of%20performing%20the%20intended%20adre